cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper focuses on computer vision tasks such as video classification, object detection/segmentation, and pose estimation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new building block for neural networks, which can be applied to various architectures, indicating that it could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions that the non-local operation can be used for capturing long-range dependencies, which is a common problem in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper presents results on video classification, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
